President Obama has nominated Edward C. DuMont to the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit. DuMont is currently a partner at the law firm WilmerHale and has a distinguished legal career in both the public and private sectors. He has argued 18 cases before the Supreme Court and has extensive experience in Supreme Court and appellate litigation. DuMont graduated from Yale University and Stanford University School of Law, and he clerked for the Honorable Richard A. Posner on the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit. He was also awarded a Luce Scholarship, which allowed him to work at a law firm in Bangkok, Thailand.